:[{"name":"Tindall","meanings":["English (Yorkshire and Lincolnshire): habitational name from Tynedale, the valley of the river Tyne, or from a place in Cumbria called Tindale, which is situated on a tributary of the South Tyne. The name derives from a British river name <i>Tina</i> (apparently from a Celtic root meaning ‘to flow’) + Old English <i>dæl</i> or Old Norse <i>dalr</i> ‘valley’."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705187,"age":69,"year":"1215","julianDay":2164830,"title":"Magna Carta","description":"King John of England agreed to a charter of rights called the Magna Carta. The document was originally drafted by the Archbishop of Canterbury to establish peace between King John and a group of rebel barons. The Magna Carta was completed in 1215 and is now considered to be one of the greatest constitutional documents of all time.","url":"https://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/education/medieval/magna-carta/","urlTitle":"National Archives - Magna Carta","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1705188,"age":78,"year":"1224","julianDay":2168117,"title":"France Declares War on England","description":"France declared war on England as Louis VIII of France attacked Poitou and northern Gascony.","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1705189,"age":113,"year":"1259","julianDay":2180901,"title":"100 Years of Conflict Between England and France Ends","description":"Treaty of Paris was signed on December 4, 1259, which ended 100 years of conflict between England and France.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Treaty_of_Paris_(1259)","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Treaty of Paris 1259","jurisdictionLevel":1}],"lifeSummary":"When Hadawise de Tynedale was born about 1146, in Lancashire, England, her father, Baron Adam de Tyndale I, was -8 and her mother, Helewise Tyndale, was -13. She married Sir William de Featherstone of Featherstonehaugh before 1168, in England. They were the parents of at least 1 son."},"et":{"about 1146–":"umbes 1146–Surnud","1146–Female":"1146–Surnud","1180–1250":"1180–1250","1185–1